Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

THR 150: Global Ancient Theater History. 3 credits.
This course examines global developments in theater from its beginnings through the 5th century CE. Students explore performance traditions and dramatic works, along with the social, historical and cultural contexts that shaped them. Offered by Theatre. Limited to three attempts.
Mason Core: Arts
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

THR 151: Global Medieval Theater History. 3 credits.
This course examines global developments in theater from the 6th through 14th centuries. Students explore performance traditions and dramatic works, along with the social, historical and cultural contexts that shaped them. Offered by Theatre. Limited to three attempts.
Mason Core: Arts
Schedule Type: Lecture
